# 2. 自分らしくいられるように

Mizuki: Heya! How's everyone doing? Good?
Len: Oh, you're all here...
Miku: Does this mean your new song's finished...?
Ena: No, we just came to take a break.
Miku: I see...
Miku: Is Mafuyu still not able to come...?
Kanade: No... She can't do much in the evening now.
Miku: I see...
Luka: But you're trying to think of a way to help her, no?
Kanade: Yes, we are...
Ena: We've tried several ideas, but...
Len: Several ideas...? Like what?
Mizuki: So, for example... We've been trying to find ways to meet her more often when she's out and stuff. That way she can feel a little more at ease.
Mizuki: Also, we've been trying to have meetings at a cafe or a diner when she's coming home from school.
Ena: And... You've been trying to compose more songs faster, right, Kanade?
Kanade: I have. Because I firmly believe that Mafuyu needs the time we use to make songs as N25.
Kanade: At the same time...
Len: Kanade...?
Kanade: We haven't been able to solve the core issue.
Kanade: She hasn't been able to work every day, but she always seems to feel relieved whenever she gets to see us...
Kanade: But we don't have the power to immediately improve her current situation.
Len: Right...
Ena: Ideally, we'd be able to convince Mafuyu's mom to accept what we're doing...
Mizuki: But that sounds impossible based on what you told us, Kanade...
Ena: Then, is there anything we can do right now...?
Luka: Yes, I believe there is.
Kanade: What?
Luka: I suspect that you've already considered it as an option.
Luka: In the end, you'll need to make Mafuyu break herself out of this situation.
Mizuki: ...!
Luka: I have a feeling that Mafuyu will be able to muster up the courage to fight back once she understands what her mom is doing to her. So, I would tell Mafuyu that straight away...
Kanade: Yes, Luka, you're right. We've already considered that...
Kanade: But... We can't do that...
Luka: Oh? Why's that?
Kanade: Because... We'd be asking far too much of Mafuyu... I doubt she'd immediately understand...
Luka: Too much? Oh...
Luka: Right. Mafuyu probably wouldn't be able to process what her mother has said.
Luka: Especially since the person who she believes has her best interests in mind simply doesn't care about her happiness.
Luka: Unfortunately, if you wish to get her out of this situation, then she will need to deal with the painful truth...
Kanade: But...
Kanade: I want to avoid that as much as possible.
Luka: Of course, you all have every right to wish for that.
Luka: However...
Luka: There may come a time when you won't be left with any other choice.
Kanade: ...
Mizuki: (Luka's right...)
Mizuki: (Up until now, we've been able to help Mafuyu feel a little better... But we haven't been able to actually change anything.)
Mizuki: (There probably are better ideas out there, but we're struggling to come up with them...)
Mizuki: (Which sort of means that we'll need to keep Luka's solution in mind moving forward.)
Mizuki: (Also...)
Mizuki: (If we don't act soon, Mafuyu's mom is probably gonna really start trying to keep us away from her daughter...)
Mizuki: (Which is only going to put Mafuyu in an even worse place...)
Mizuki: (At the same time, Kanade's right... I doubt Mafuyu's in a state right now where she can properly process the truth.)
Mizuki: (What are we supposed to do...?)
Mizuki: <Alright, I'm gonna get back to work...>
Mizuki: We couldn't come up with any good ideas...
Mizuki: Mafuyu...?
Mafuyu's Message: <Sorry for not responding sooner, but I won't be able to do anything today. I'll try working on my lyrics tomorrow if I have time.>
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (She's probably sending us this while her mom's not watching...)
Mizuki: (Even at home, she's a prisoner... What in the world does that feel like?)
Mizuki: (Home was a place of refuge for me... I could just be myself here.)
Mizuki: (In or outside of home, Mafuyu's not allowed to be herself. On top of that, her time with us—the one place she could escape—has been taken away from her...)
Mizuki: (She has nowhere to run.)
Mizuki: (If she has to keep enduring this...)
Mizuki: That'd be horrible...
Mizuki: (Seriously, isn't there anything we can do...?)
Mizuki: (It doesn't have to be big. Just some time that allows Mafuyu to be herself.)
Mizuki: (Time... For her to be herself...)
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (Isn't there a way to get her family to understand...? Like the way mine did for me...)
Mizuki: (Mom, Dad and Sis all took the time to understand when I really needed a place to run.)
Mizuki: (Because they did, I could just be myself at home.)
Mizuki: (Yeah... What if we could work with her for little bits at a time...?)
Mizuki: (But her mom's watching her like a hawk... The only time we could work together would be...)
Mizuki: Oh...!
Mizuki: <K! Enanan! Sorry, I know you're both working, but can we chat for a second?>
Mizuki: <I just came up with a really good idea!>
